Rules For Subjunctive
//(if does not follow any other suffix) or AGR1 (person-number)
// 1. AGR2+Future+this  2. this only (subjunctive)
ो  / [x,x,2p,x,x,x] / VC or Ve
ओ  / [x,x,2p,x,x,x] / Vaa or Vo or Vuu or Vii or caus or trans
 ूँ  or ूं / [x,sg,1p,x,x,x] / VC or Ve
// ूँ  / [x,sg,1p,x,x,x] / VC or Ve
ऊँ or ऊं or उं / [x,sg,1p,x,x,x] / Vaa or Vo or Vuu or Vii or caus or trans
  े  / [x,sg,2p,x,x,(+imperative : +intimate)] or [x,sg,3p,x,x,x] / VC or Ve
  ें  / [x,pl,2p,x,x,(+imperative : +polite)] or [x,pl,3p,x,x,x] / VC or Ve
ए  or ये / [x,sg,2p,x,x,(+imperative : intimate)] or [x,sg,3p,x,x,x] / Vaa or Vo or Vuu or Vii or caus or trans
एँ  / [x,pl,2p,x,x,(+imperative : polite)] or [x,pl,3p,x,x,x] / Vaa or Vo or Vuu or Vii or caus or trans
एं or यें / [x,pl,(1p : 2phon : 3p),x,x,(Imperative: Honorific)] or [x,pl,(1p : 2phon : 3p),x,x,x] / Vaa or Vo or Vuu or Vii or caus or trans

